definitions.definition: A member of a church separated from the Church of England ; a Protestant dissenter .
Loosely, a Christian who does not conform to the doctrines of an established church .
Someone who does not conform to accepted beliefs , customs or practices .

main_definition: A member of a church separated from the Church of England ; a Protestant dissenter . [from 17th c.]
secondary_definitions: Loosely, a Christian who does not conform to the doctrines of an established church . [from 17th c.]
